<|startoftext|>Dish: mexican omelette diavolo
Directions: dice the meat into small chunks and set aside in the fridge to keep from getting too dry during the cooking process
preheat the oven to 350 degrees
heat the butter and sause , in a pan
add the onion and saute for about 3 minutes until soft
add the green chilies , then allspice and saute for about 5 minutes more until soft and a little darker in colour
add the tomatoes and saute until the tomatoes have reduced by half
season again with salt and sugar if you think you need to add salt
pour the eggs into the pan and scramble
pour all of the tomato mixture over the bottom of a buttered casserole dish
you will need to flip and stir a few times
put the casserole in the oven and bake for 45 minutes
take the dish out and uncover and baste with the sauce
continue baking until the omelette is firm all the way through and cooked through , but the centre will still be firm when you lift the edge of the lid
allow to cool for about 20-30 minutes before serving using some of the leftover sauce to top the dish , if desired'<|endoftext|>
